  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents a credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research contexts to inform ventricular assist device design decisions. A full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 5. Seven factors were assessed with achieved levels below required levels; six factors were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. Despite identified gaps, the assessment team accepted the model for its intended use given the low-consequence decision context and supplementary experimental corroboration from peer-reviewed literature. The intended-use scope is conveyed through this narrative description rather than a structured ContextOfUse object.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v2",
